yclingtips-1-1-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-review-cyclingtips-1-1-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-review-cyclingtips-1-1-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-review-cyclingtips-1-1-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-review-cyclingtips-1-1-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-review-cyclingtips-1-1.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">The Pro Team Digital alongside a number of equally high-end 1/4-inch torque wrenches. This digital model offers a more comfortable hold, a smaller head for tight areas, and better accuracy than most. </figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-versus-Topeak-2-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"483894\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-versus-Topeak-2.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=483894\" class=\"wp-image-483894\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-versus-Topeak-2-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-versus-Topeak-2-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-versus-Topeak-2-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-versus-Topeak-2-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-versus-Topeak-2-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-versus-Topeak-2.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">The Pro Team Digital and Topeak D-Torq are certainly from the same manufacturer, however, they&#8217;re not identical. </figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-review-cyclingtips-2-1-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"483659\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=483659\" class=\"wp-image-483659\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-review-cyclingtips-2-1-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-review-cyclingtips-2-1-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-review-cyclingtips-2-1-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-review-cyclingtips-2-1-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-review-cyclingtips-2-1-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-review-cyclingtips-2-1.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">Much like the Topeak D-Torq, the Pro Team Digital was an exact match to my torque wrench test machine.</figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-versus-Topeak-1-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"483891\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Pro-Team-Digital-Torque-Wrench-versu